cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper focuses on the analysis of the shape bias property of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) in image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the role of different factors such as model architecture, initialization, and regularization techniques, which are related to machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The use of negative images and the investigation of the generalization ability of CNNs suggest a focus on neural networks and their behavior, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the impact of batch normalization on the shape bias property, which is related to natural language processing and text classification, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
